ine that uses CSS layouts to manage user interfaces across platforms. </p>\n<p>In this talk, we learn about Yoga's main concepts and use-cases. Then, we will build a demo app for React Native and Android to showcase the reusability of Yoga.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Cross-Platform CSS (Yes, it's Possible!) with Yoga","date":"Jan 01, 2021"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/talks/2021/cross-platform-css-with-yoga/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/talks/2021/10000-steps-of-open-source-project-health/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The 10,000 Steps of Open Source Project Health"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/talks/2021/hands-on-react-native/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Hands-on React Native: From Zero to Hero"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2125292342","2915660680","3649515864","63159454"]}